It was a gruesome start to the New Year in Umbumbulu, south of Durban, after the body of a woman (29) was discovered at Ndaya Reserve on New Year’s Day. The shot and battered murder victim has been identified as Zinhle Muthwa. Police spokesperson, Cpt Nqobile Gwala said, “It is alleged that on 1 January 2020 at 09:55, a body was found at Ndaya Reserve in Umbumbulu next to the road with head injuries and bruises all over the body. She also sustained a gunshot wound to the head. A case of murder was opened at Umbumbulu SAPS for further investigation.” “On 4 January 2020, Umbumbulu Detectives led by the station commander followed up information regarding the suspect involved in the murder. A 30-year-old suspect was traced and arrested in the Umbumbulu area after an intensive investigation. A firearm suspected to be used in the commission of an offence was also confiscated by police,” said Gwala. The suspect is expected to appear in the Umbumbulu Magistrates’ Court today, 6 January 2020. The KwaZulu-Natal Provincial Commissioner, Lieutenant General Khombinkosi Jula welcomed the arrest of the suspect and praised the investigative team for their dedication in arresting the suspect.